parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and coolant leaks can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. Coolant leaks can also cause engine damage and overheating, leading to costly repairs.
symptoms: engine taking a long time to warm up

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the intake manifold gasket can cause coolant leaks, engine stalling, and loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: engine taking a long time to warm up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the head gasket can cause coolant leaks, engine stalling, and loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: engine taking a long time to warm up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the pump control module can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Electrical system failures can cause the engine to stall, lights and instruments to malfunction, and safety systems to fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Line Failure due to Proximity to Exhaust System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake line can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to drive, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the vehicle is unable to engage into reverse or drive
the vehicle makes a loud grinding noise
the vehicle moves at a slow pace
the transmission fluid level is low.
